    <text>
      <body>
        <div type="letter">
            <div type="text">
                <opener>
                    <placeName>London</placeName>
                    <date>25 April 1856</date>
                    <salute>My dear sir</salute>
                </opener>
                <div type="transcription">
                     
                  <p>I have desired Mess<hi rend="superscript">rs</hi> Longman to send you by rail 6 Copies of a cheap Ed. <hi rend="superscript">n</hi> I am bringing out of our Introduction “at price cost &amp; under” one of which I will thank you to accept yourself &amp; to present another in my name to the Ipswich Museum, leaving the remaining Copies for prizes at your next Hortic <hi rend="superscript">.l</hi>. Exhibition, or as you think best. As my object is simply making Entomological comments you can’t go wrong. You will see that I give plenty for the money — 40 hours’ tough reading (as I know from each stint having taken me just an hour’s reading when correcting the proofs) for 5/.</p>
                  <p>I am | my dear Sir | yours very truly | W. Spence</p> 
                </div>
            </div>

        </div>
        
      </body>
